    "description": "An ancient settlement near Hippo Regius. It was an ancient bishopric and is mentioned in Augustine's letters in the context of the Donatist controversy. BAtlas declined to place it on a map.",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: near Hippo Regius. Wikipedia (as of April 2026) asserts an identification with \"ruins at Ain-Tebla in modern Algeria\", but cites no sources.</p>",
